HEADWORD: Fimbricate
<hw>Fim"bri*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Fringed; jagged; fimbriate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>fringed, on one side only, by
long, straight hairs, as the antenn⟦ae⟧ of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fin</ent>⟦br⟧
